#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:2
msgid "discover_tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:6
msgid ""
"Register tests with names and properties discovered at test time by :manual:"
"`ctest(1)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:9
msgid ""
"discover_tests(COMMAND <command> [<arg>...] [COMMAND_EXPAND_LISTS]\n"
"  [CONFIGURATIONS <config>...]\n"
"  DISCOVERY_ARGS <arg>...\n"
"  DISCOVERY_MATCH <regex>\n"
"  [DISCOVERY_PROPERTIES <key> <value> [<key> <value>]...]\n"
"  TEST_NAME <replacement>\n"
"  TEST_ARGS <replacement>...\n"
"  [TEST_PROPERTIES <key> <replacement> [<key> <replacement>]...]\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:21
msgid ""
"This command configures test discovery rather than defining a single test at "
"configure time.  During test execution, :manual:`ctest(1)` runs the "
"specified discovery command, parses its output, and registers one or more "
"tests based on the provided regular expression and replacement strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:26
msgid "``discover_tests`` options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:28
msgid "``COMMAND``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:29
msgid "Specify the command-line used for test discovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:31
msgid ""
"The command is executed by :manual:`ctest(1)` at test time (not by CMake at "
"configure time).  With ``DISCOVERY_ARGS`` appended, it must print the list "
"of available tests in a format matched by ``DISCOVERY_MATCH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:35
msgid ""
"If ``<command>`` specifies an executable target created by :command:"
"`add_executable`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:38
msgid ""
"It will automatically be replaced by the location of the executable created "
"at build time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:41
msgid ""
"The target's :prop_tgt:`CROSSCOMPILING_EMULATOR`, if set, will be used to "
"run the command on the host::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:44
msgid "<emulator> <command>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:46
msgid ""
"The emulator is used only when :variable:`cross-compiling "
"<CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:49
msgid ""
"The target's :prop_tgt:`TEST_LAUNCHER`, if set, will be used to launch the "
"command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:52
msgid "<launcher> <command>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:54
msgid "If the :prop_tgt:`CROSSCOMPILING_EMULATOR` is also set, both are used::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:56
msgid "<launcher> <emulator> <command>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:58
msgid ""
"The command may be specified using :manual:`generator expressions <cmake-"
"generator-expressions(7)>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:61
msgid "``COMMAND_EXPAND_LISTS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:62
msgid ""
"Lists in ``COMMAND`` arguments will be expanded, including those created "
"with :manual:`generator expressions <cmake-generator-expressions(7)>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:65
msgid "``CONFIGURATIONS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:66
msgid "Restrict the test discovery only to the named configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:68
msgid "``DISCOVERY_ARGS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:69
msgid "Additional arguments passed to ``COMMAND`` when performing discovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:71
msgid "``DISCOVERY_MATCH``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:72
msgid ""
"Regular expression used to parse each line produced by the discovery "
"command. Capturing groups may be referenced by ``TEST_NAME``, ``TEST_ARGS``, "
"and values in ``TEST_PROPERTIES`` using ``\\1``, ``\\2``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:76
msgid "``DISCOVERY_PROPERTIES``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:77
msgid "Specify properties for the discovery run itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:79
msgid "``TEST_NAME``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:80
msgid ""
"Replacement string used to generate the test name for each discovered test. "
"It may reference capture groups from ``DISCOVERY_MATCH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:83
msgid "``TEST_ARGS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:84
msgid ""
"Replacement strings used to generate the arguments passed to the discovered "
"test.  Each argument may reference capture groups from ``DISCOVERY_MATCH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:87
msgid "``TEST_PROPERTIES``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:88
msgid ""
"Specify test properties to set on each discovered test.  Values are "
"replacement strings and may reference capture groups from "
"``DISCOVERY_MATCH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:92
msgid ""
"CTest executes the discovery step to obtain the list of tests and then runs "
"each discovered test using the command-line produced by ``COMMAND`` together "
"with ``TEST_ARGS``.  The pass/fail behavior of each discovered test follows "
"the usual CTest rules (exit code ``0`` indicates success unless inverted by "
"the :prop_test:`WILL_FAIL` property). Output written to stdout or stderr is "
"captured by :manual:`ctest(1)` and only affects the pass/fail status via "
"the :prop_test:`PASS_REGULAR_EXPRESSION`, :prop_test:"
"`FAIL_REGULAR_EXPRESSION`, or :prop_test:`SKIP_REGULAR_EXPRESSION` test "
"properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:101
msgid "Example usage:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:103
msgid ""
"discover_tests(COMMAND testDriver --exe $<TARGET_FILE:myexe>\n"
"  DISCOVERY_ARGS --list-tests\n"
"  DISCOVERY_MATCH \"^([^,]+),([^,]+),([^,]+),(.*)$\"\n"
"  TEST_NAME \"${PROJECT_NAME}.\\\\1.\\\\2\"\n"
"  TEST_ARGS --run-test \"\\\\1.\\\\2\"\n"
"  TEST_PROPERTIES\n"
"    PROCESSORS \"\\\\3\"\n"
"    LABELS \"\\\\4\"\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/discover_tests.rst:115
msgid ""
"This example configures discovery by running ``testDriver --list-tests``. "
"For each line of output that matches ``DISCOVERY_MATCH``, a test name is "
"generated using ``TEST_NAME``, the per-test command-line is generated using "
"``TEST_ARGS``, and test properties are populated from the remaining capture "
"groups."
msgstr ""
